Hello all,
      I know I =
do not post much here, so let me start.  Going along these lines of thought=
, if you are recording the questions onto an audio tape and leaving 20 seco=
nds of silence between them, you are still recording you and possibly your =
thoughts as well as any spirits that might be around you or your recording =
environment at that time.  So how do you know that what you listen back on =
is from the location you placed the recorder in and not from the location y=
ou recorded the questions in or from your own creation?  Just something to =
think about.

  Lynn



Tracy &lt;loneshewolf999@ yahoo.com&gt; wrote:
  =
      I am not sure this would still rule it out.  I don&#39;t think psychokine=
sis is restrained by walls, the mind isn&#39;t restrained by walls whether huma=
n or deceased.  I am guessing that psychokinesis behaves similar to telepat=
hy... .

  I believe many evp&#39;s are deceased spirits, but the question o=
n whether it could be a living person imprinting the evps was certainly one=
 that made me really think !  

Frank Ratka &lt;warrior18eii@ yahoo.com&gt; wrote=
:
          Hi James,

Back when I still investigated haunted sites, our te=
am did this on various occasions within a house where we recorded several h=
ours of activity over a few years (a long term investigation) . We would le=
ave our audio equipment recording in several &quot;hot spots&quot; all over the house=
 and then leave for an hour or two. I have to say, in our experience we nev=
er got an EVP while we were out of the house. As a matter of fact we had an=
 EVP when we reentered the house saying, &quot;here they come, lets go&quot;. I don&#39;t=
 necessarily understand why a ghost or spirit would talk with no one presen=
t to receive the message unless during setup you explained what you are try=
ing to accomplish and what the spirits roll is in the experiment (we never =
tried explaining). A piece of machinery (recorders) in an empty room does n=
ot have a consciousness or spiritual presence I would be interested to see =
if you get different results.

Regards,

Frank


